ANTHRAX, HUMAN - AUSTRALIA (QUEENSLAND)
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Anthrax - Australia (Victoria) 970211180535
Anthrax - Australia (Victoria) (09) 970603120952
Date: Thu, 6 Aug 1998 09:25:43 -0400
Source: [ex The Austrailian,
<http://www.theaustrailan.com.au/state/4272098.htm>
Via: Robertson, George <GRobertson@magentabio.com>

The case of a young man who contracted Anthrax is the first to be notified
in Queensland in more than 50 years. Health Minister Wendy Edmond told
state parliament it was extremely rare for humans to be infected by
cutaneous anthrax.
Queensland Health had assessed no risk to the public because it could not
be transmitted between humans. Nor was there any risk to livestock, she said.
A young labourer was admitted to Brisbane's Princess Alexandra Hospital on
July 18 with a diagnosis of cellulitis. Cutaneous anthrax was diagnosed 10
days later, Ms Edmond said, and is doing well. However, Ms Edmond said the
patient had not been exposed to animals, and Queensland Health was
investigating the source of the infection.
Possible sources, such as exposure to cotton bales, fertiliser, playing
rugby football or in a home environment were being investigated.
--
