[I contacted Rod Thomas immediately on the receipt of the above and he
kindly replied as follows: - Mod.MHJ
Date: Fri, 7 Aug 1998 15:35:46 +1000
From: Thomas, Rod <ThomasR@prose.dpi.qld.gov.au>

Jackie Harper at Princess Alexandra Hospital rang a couple of times re
identification of the organism, said basically what you have posted.
Patient first presented with small abscess on his backside. No recent farm
contact. Is a young (18 according to a news report) fork-lift driver and
had been recently shifting fertiliser and hessian bales of cotton.
Queensland Health has been doing the epidemiology, apparently no source
identified so far. Queensland DPI's emergency response veterinarian, Ian
Douglas (douglasi@dpi.qld.gov.au), has been liaising with the Health
Department. I couldn't get him on the phone just now, but heard him on the
radio this morning saying that the source has not been determined.
We have not seen any cases of anthrax in animals in Queensland since the
1993 case near Rockhampton.
--
Rod Thomas
Dept of Primary Industries
Queensland
e-mail: ThomasR@prose.dpi.qld.gov.au
